---
title: Szechuan Chicken & Pineapple Stir-Fry with Ginger, Bell Pepper & Peanuts
description: Falling into a stir-fry rut with the same veggie + sauce combo each week? We’ve got you covered. This version features chicken breast strips, pineapple, scallions, and bell pepper, which are simmered with a zingy, spicy, and sweet blend of Szechuan paste, pineapple juice, and citrusy ponzu. It’s all spooned over ginger rice and garnished with peanuts for crunch. The best part? It’s ready in just 30 minutes from start to finish—now that’s what we call a winning dinner.
